## 1. Description

This threat model covers the live trading execution pipeline, including broker API integration, order management, position tracking, and real-time risk controls.

## 2. Assets

| Asset | Classification | Impact if Compromised |
|-------|----------------|----------------------|
| Broker API credentials | Restricted | Critical -- unauthorized trades |
| Trading account balance | Restricted | Critical -- financial loss |
| Position state | Confidential | High -- incorrect risk exposure |
| Order history | Confidential | High -- regulatory violation |
| Strategy parameters | Confidential | Medium -- alpha leakage |
| Market data feeds | Internal | Medium -- trading on stale data |

## 3. Data Flow

```
Market Data Feed -> Strategy Engine -> Risk Manager -> Order Router -> Broker API
                                                                         |
State Store <-- Position Tracker <-- Fill Handler <-- Execution Report --+
```

### Trust Boundaries

| Boundary | Description | Controls |
|----------|-------------|----------|
| Broker API | External network boundary | TLS, API key auth, IP allowlist |
| Strategy -> Risk | Internal logic boundary | Risk limits enforced before execution |
| Risk -> Execution | Approval boundary | No order without risk approval |
| Market Data | External feed boundary | Staleness detection, validation |

## 4. Threat Actors

| Actor | Capability | Motivation | Likelihood |
|-------|------------|------------|------------|
| External Attacker | Network access, public exploits | Financial gain, credential theft | Medium |
| Compromised Dependency | Code execution via supply chain | Data exfiltration | Low |
| Rogue Strategy | Excessive trading, loss generation | Misconfiguration | Medium |
| Stale Data Feed | Delayed/incorrect market data | Infrastructure failure | Medium |

## 5. Attack Vectors

### Vector 1: Broker Credential Theft

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| Description | Attacker obtains broker API keys and executes unauthorized trades |
| Prerequisites | Access to environment variables, config files, or memory |
| STRIDE Category | Spoofing / Elevation of Privilege |
| Likelihood | Medium |
| Impact | Critical |
| Risk Score | High |

**Mitigation:**
- [ ] Store credentials in secrets manager (Vault, AWS Secrets Manager)
- [ ] Rotate API keys regularly (90-day maximum)
- [ ] IP allowlisting on broker API
- [ ] Separate read-only and trading API keys
- [ ] Audit all credential access

### Vector 2: Runaway Strategy (Excessive Orders)

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| Description | Misconfigured strategy generates excessive orders causing financial loss |
| Prerequisites | Strategy deployment without proper risk limits |
| STRIDE Category | Denial of Service (financial) |
| Likelihood | Medium |
| Impact | High |
| Risk Score | High |

**Mitigation:**
- [ ] Per-strategy order rate limits
- [ ] Daily loss limits with automatic kill switch
- [ ] Maximum position size limits
- [ ] Maximum number of open positions
- [ ] Human approval for strategy parameter changes

### Vector 3: Market Data Manipulation

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| Description | Corrupted or delayed market data leads to incorrect trading decisions |
| Prerequisites | Feed latency, provider outage, or man-in-the-middle |
| STRIDE Category | Tampering |
| Likelihood | Medium |
| Impact | High |
| Risk Score | Medium |

**Mitigation:**
- [ ] Staleness detection (reject data older than threshold)
- [ ] Cross-feed validation (compare multiple sources)
- [ ] Automatic halt on data quality degradation
- [ ] Default to conservative mode when data quality is low

### Vector 4: State Corruption

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| Description | Position state becomes inconsistent between modules, leading to incorrect risk calculations |
| Prerequisites | Race condition, partial write, or crash during state update |
| STRIDE Category | Tampering / Repudiation |
| Likelihood | Low |
| Impact | Critical |
| Risk Score | Medium |

**Mitigation:**
- [ ] Single source of truth for position state
- [ ] Idempotent state updates
- [ ] Periodic reconciliation with broker
- [ ] Audit trail for all state changes
- [ ] Crash recovery from journal log

